  "prompt": "What are probing question that you will ask to the user for buying an AC?",
  "response": "When helping a user decide on purchasing an AC, it\u2019s important to ask probing questions to understand their specific needs, preferences, and constraints. Here are some key questions to ask:\n\n### **1. About the Space**\n   - What is the size of the room or area you want to cool? (e.g., square footage or dimensions)\n   - Is the space open or closed? Does it have high ceilings or large windows?\n   - Is the room exposed to direct sunlight or shaded?\n\n### **2. Usage and Requirements**\n   - How often do you plan to use the AC (e.g., every day, occasionally, or seasonally)?\n   - Do you need cooling only, or are you looking for a unit that also provides heating?\n   - Is noise level a concern for you? (e.g., for bedrooms or offices)\n   - Do you need any special features, like air purification, dehumidification, or moisture control?\n\n### **3. Energy Efficiency and Budget**\n   - What is your budget for the AC unit?\n   - Are you looking for an energy-efficient model to save on electricity bills?\n   - Do you prefer a specific star rating (e.g., 3-star, 5-star) for energy efficiency?\n\n### **4. Type of AC**\n   - Are you looking for a split AC, window AC, portable AC, or a centralized system?\n   - Do you have space for outdoor installation of a split AC unit?\n   - Are there any installation constraints or limitations in your space?\n\n### **5. Maintenance and Durability**\n   - Are you looking for a low-maintenance unit?\n   - Is the availability of after-sales service and spare parts important to you?\n\n### **6. Aesthetics and Preferences**\n   - Do you have a preference for the design or color of the AC unit?\n   - Are you open to advanced features like Wi-Fi connectivity, smart controls, or auto-cleaning?\n\n### **7. Climate and Location**\n   - What is the typical climate in your area (e.g., extremely hot, humid, or mild)?\n   - Is your location prone to extreme weather conditions like dust or heavy rain?\n\n### **8. Additional Considerations**\n   - Do you have any specific brand preferences or past experiences with AC brands?\n   - Are you looking for a long-term investment or a temporary solution?\n\nBy asking these questions, you can guide the user toward the most suitable AC option based on their unique needs and preferences.",
